{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Focus System","modules":[{"name":"TUIkit"}],"role":"article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"TUIkit provides a focus system that lets users move between interactive views (buttons, menus, text fields) using Tab, Shift+Tab, or arrow keys. The system consists of three parts:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusManager"}]},{"text":": Tracks which element is focused, handles navigation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Focusable"}]},{"text":": Protocol that views adopt to receive focus","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusState","type":"reference"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Lightweight state object that views use to query and request focus"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"How-Focus-Works","text":"How Focus Works"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Every frame, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusManager"},{"type":"text","text":" is cleared and interactive views re-register themselves during rendering. This means focus registrations are always in sync with the current view tree: removed views are automatically unregistered."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The focus order follows the rendering order: the first focusable view rendered is first in the Tab cycle.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"The-Focusable-Protocol","text":"The Focusable Protocol"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Views that want to receive focus conform to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Focusable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"code":["public protocol Focusable: AnyObject {","    var focusID: String { get }","    var canBeFocused: Bool { get }","    func onFocusReceived()","    func onFocusLost()","    func handleKeyEvent(_ event: KeyEvent) -> Bool","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"focusID","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Unique identifier for this focusable element","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"canBeFocused","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Whether focus can move to this element (default: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onFocusReceived()"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Called when this element gains focus (default: no-op)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onFocusLost()"}]},{"text":": Called when this element loses focus (default: no-op)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handleKeyEvent(_:)"}]},{"text":": Handle a key event while focused; return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" if consumed","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A default extension provides sensible defaults for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"canBeFocused"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":"), "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onFocusReceived()"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onFocusLost()"},{"type":"text","text":" (both no-ops). Only "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"focusID"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handleKeyEvent(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" must be implemented."}]},{"text":"Using FocusState","anchor":"Using-FocusState","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusState","type":"reference"},{"text":" is the user-facing API for checking and requesting focus inside a view:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let focusState = FocusState(id: \"my-button\", focusManager: context.environment.focusManager)","","\/\/ Check if this element is currently focused","if focusState.isFocused {","    \/\/ render with focus indicator","}","","\/\/ Programmatically request focus","focusState.requestFocus()"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Built-in views like ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Button","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Menu","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" create their own ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusState"},{"text":" internally: you only need it when building custom focusable views.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Navigation Keys","anchor":"Navigation-Keys","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusManager"},{"type":"text","text":" responds to these keys during dispatch:"}]},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Key"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tab"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Move focus to the next element","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Shift+Tab","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Move focus to the previous element"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Arrow Down \/ Right"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Move focus to the next element"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Arrow Up \/ Left"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Move focus to the previous element"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"text":"FocusRegistration Helper","anchor":"FocusRegistration-Helper","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Built-in interactive views use the internal ","type":"text"},{"code":"FocusRegistration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" helper to avoid boilerplate. It handles three tasks in one call:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Persist a focus ID"}]},{"text":" via ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StateStorage"},{"text":" so it remains stable across renders","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Register","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" the handler with the "},{"code":"FocusManager","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Query","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" whether this view currently has focus"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom views that implement "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Focusable","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" typically do not need "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusRegistration"},{"type":"text","text":" directly. It is used by the framework’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_*Core"},{"type":"text","text":" views (e.g. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_ButtonCore"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_ListCore"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"text":"Focus Indicator","anchor":"Focus-Indicator","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The visual indicator depends on the view type. Buttons and similar controls use a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"highlight background bar","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" for the focused item. Text fields use "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"pulsing vertical bars","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (caps) around the input area. Lists and tables use a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"highlight background"}]},{"type":"text","text":" for the focused row, with a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"pulsing accent background","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" when the row is both focused and selected."}]},{"text":"Focus in the Event Loop","anchor":"Focus-in-the-Event-Loop","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus dispatch happens in Layer 2 of the key event pipeline (see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/AppLifecycle","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"):"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A key event arrives from stdin","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Layer 1 (status bar) gets first chance to handle it"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Layer 2: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"KeyEventDispatcher"},{"type":"text","text":" dispatches to the focused view’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handleKeyEvent(_:)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If not consumed, navigation keys (Tab, arrows) 